Full Description: Benedict Research Company Ltd (BRCL) was established in 2009 in Mullingar, Co. Westmeath, to develop an innovative assembly system of joining rigid sheets of metal together, called KLIXXN.  KLIXXN’s unique selling point is a method whereby flat metal sheets simply click together without the need for nuts, bolts, screws, rivets, welding or assembly tools and are as easy to dismantle as they are to assemble. The initial KLIXXN product, currently being developed, is the KLIXXN electrical/electronic enclosure; however, the KLIXXN concept can be applied to a multitude of end products. The electrical enclosure market is estimated at €6bn in Europe alone.  KLIXXN is a generation ahead of its competitors. The technology enables speed and simplicity of assembly and disassembly, flatpack shipping and storage, tailored interchangeable components and materials, excellent sealing options and an extremely robust and aesthetically pleasing system. A unique and wide range of KLIXXN accessories allow for a fully integrated system, and with its efficient and eco-friendly low cost manufacturing, KLIXXN has had nothing but positive feedback from industry experts across the UK, Ireland and Europe.

Description: Welcome to the Texas Triangle Regional Center of Innovation and Commercialization (RCIC).
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: The Texas Triangle Regional Center of Innovation and Commercialization (Texas Triangle RCIC) serves the entrepreneurial community by helping them apply for capital with the Emerging Technology Fund and connecting these applicants with local resources. They are committed to providing the best services for entrepreneurs to build their businesses into impactful and profitable companies of the future within the Texas Triangle region. The Texas Triangle RCIC partners with a Regional Advisory Committee, composed of technical and business experts, who provide due diligence for all applications. The Texas Triangle RCIC is governed by eleven regional board members and is hosted by Research Valley Partnership, Inc., the economic development organization of Research Valley. In 2005, the Texas legislature passed the under HB 1765, establishing an investment fund for technology-based start-up ventures. The objectives of the legislation were to foster research initiatives among the State’s institutions of higher learning and encourage the development of “next generation” innovative, competitive technology companies in the State of Texas. The Emerging Technology Fund has been renewed twice; most recently with $203.5 million for the next biennium to continue the commitment to advance Texas as an entrepreneurial state through investment in commercialization ventures and applied research.

Full Description: The Oklahoma Business Roundtable serves as the state’s major economic development support organization. Comprised of over 175 top Oklahoma corporations and business organizations, the Roundtable provides important business development advice and assistance to the Governor, Lt. Governor  the Oklahoma Department of Commerce and other state economic development partners. Now in its 23rd year, the Oklahoma Business Roundtable serves as the state’s primary economic development “support” organization – providing vital funding to assist business retention, expansion, recruitment and company start-up efforts.  They are a 501(c)(6)Today,  non-profit organization which supports the work of their Governor, Lt. Governor, Commerce Department and statewide partners.   It takes all of us, public and private, working together for the common good, to make a difference in their state. The desire to be a part of Oklahoma’s innovative economic solution is what draws their members, who represent key manufacturing, financial, energy, education and development organizations. The Roundtable helps fund important business promotion activities to spur the expansion and recruitment of new business in Oklahoma. This includes hosting prospects, site location consultants and dignitaries; assisting trade and investment missions; promoting Oklahoma; providing marketing materials; and sponsoring business development events when state appropriated monies cannot be used. Roundtable members also play a key role in contacting and hosting both domestic and international clients. Their support for their state’s economic development leadership assisted their efforts in creating over 7600 new jobs and 1.9 billion in investment in FY 2014. What will this year bring?

Full Description: KNOWLEDGE NATION - NEW EDUCATIONAL GAMES VENTURE ANNOUNCED The Directors of Entellect Solutions Ltd (ESN or the Company) announce that Knowledge Nation Inc. (â€œKNIâ€) â€“ a US incorporated and San Francisco based educational games and learning initiator - will become a subsidiary of the Company under the terms of the recently announced collaboration with Mooter Media Limited (Mooter) and Hot Shot Media Ltd (Hot Shot). KNI will be a major development arm of the joint educational collaboration between ESN, Mooter, and Hot Shot. Subject to final determination by the co-developers, the collaboration will be established through a Singapore registered joint venture (â€œKnowledge Nation Pte Ltd or â€œKNJVâ€). The equity holders in KNJV will be Entellect: 60%, Mooter: 20% and Hot Shot: 20%. Entellect is listed on the Australian Securities Exchange (ASX) with the code ESN. Mooter is listed on both the ASX (listing code: MMZ) and the OTCQX in the US (listing code: MOTMY). Hot Shot is a Singaporean incorporated and based, unlisted public corporation. The KNJV will be the parent entity for the development, marketing and implementation of the co-venturersâ€™ unique suite of interactive educational games, learning initiatives and educational derivatives. Professor Paul Fullwood, who is internationally recognised as a pioneer in the educational games arena and a highly experienced educational strategist, will be appointed as the Senior Advisor to KNJV. Professor Fullwood was the product development initiator and VicePresident of Nasdaq listed, education success story, Lightspan Inc. Professor Fullwood was the Professor and First Chair of Computer Games Technology at the University of Abertay in Scotland and a Director of IC-CAVE (the International Centre for Computer Arts and Virtual Entertainment), a European Union funded video games research centre. Professor Fullwood was also Vice President and Head of World-Wide Studios for Hasbro Interactive and a founder and President of Accent Media Productions. Mr. Robin Matthews has been appointed Studio Head of KNI and the new venture. Mr.Mathews has over 20 years of games development experience. A lawyer and former Studio Head at Microprose in the US, Mr. Mathews has held senior positions at Electronic Arts, Disney/Walker Digital, Hasbro Interactive, EAI, Sirtech and most recently, Namco Bandai Games as Director of Development and Head of their San Diego studio. He also founded a hi-tech company, pioneering innovative concepts within the teaching and training arenas in the NFL/NCAA and in other sporting and social gaming fields. Commenting on the new venture, Professor Fullwood said: â€œI am absolutely delighted to be part of this very exciting concept and to join with the other founding partners in bringing this extremely important educational advancement project to fruition. Having been involved, from the commencement, in Lightspan Inc., a company that found enormous financial and academic success, I know directly how specially created educational games can be highly productive and highly profitable. We have been planning and working on this project for some time now and have achieved significant advancement. The opportunities in this field are almost limitless in scope. With the team we are putting together to implement our vision I am particularly confident that this venture will find early and substantial successâ€.

Description: HCB Bancshares was organized at the direction of the Board of Directors of the Bank for the purpose of becoming a holding company.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: HCB Bancshares, Inc. operates as the holding company for HEARTLAND Community Bank. The Bank's principal lending activity consists of the origination of loans collateralized by mortgages on single-family residences in its primary market area; and commercial real estate and multifamily properties in the State of Arkansas. It also makes a variety of consumer and commercial business loans. The commercial real estate loans may be collateralized by offices, warehouses, shopping centers, land, nursing homes, single-family subdivision developments, and other commercial properties. The consumer loans primarily consist of loans collateralized by savings deposits at the Bank and automobiles. Besides, the investment activities of the Bank consist primarily of investments in mortgage-backed securities and other investment securities, consisting primarily of securities issued or guaranteed by the U.S. government or agencies thereof, and state and municipal securities. Further, it attracts deposits principally from within its primary market area by offering NOW accounts, money market accounts, statement savings accounts, individual retirement accounts, and certificates of deposit. The Bank's primary market area comprises the Calhoun, Cleveland, Dallas, Grant, Ouachita, and Saline counties in Arkansas. To a lesser extent, it accepts savings deposits and offers loans throughout the remainder of central and southern Arkansas. As of June 30, 2003, the Bank operated through five banking offices located in Camden, Fordyce, Sheridan, and Bryant in Arkansas.
